\u8eab\u9ad4\u5168\u90e8\u958b\u653e\u4e86\u300f\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n\n=== Golden Melody ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"background: rgb(255, 255, 255); margin-bottom: 109px;\" width=\"50%\"\n!Year \n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Album\n! Result\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2015\n| Best Lyricist\n| Lala Hsu\uff0f''Missing''\n|''Missing''\u300e\u5c0b\u4eba\u555f\u4e8b\u300f|| {{nom}}\n|}\n\n=== Association of Musicians in Taiwan ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\" \n! colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | Top ten singles\n|- style=\"height: 40px;\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Year\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Song title\n! colspan=\"2\" |Contribution\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Singer\n! rowspan=\"2\" |note\n|-\n!Lyrics\n!Comp.\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2014 \n| ''Missing'' (\u5c0b\u4eba\u555f\u4e8b) ||{{yes}}\n|<br> \n|[[Lala Hsu]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ent.ltn.com.tw/news/breakingnews/1340943|title=Hush\u5165\u570d\u6700\u4f73\u4f5c\u8a5e\u4eba \u611f\u8b1d\u71d5\u59ff\u958b\u555f\u5275\u4f5c\u8def|last=\u8521\u741b\u5100|date=June 6, 2015|work=Liberty Times|language=zh-hant|access-date=29 June 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Kepler'' (\u514b\u535c\u52d2) ||{{yes}}|| {{yes}} \n|[[Stephanie Sun]]\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hush}}\n[[Category:LGBT singers]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese lyricists]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese male singers]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese Mandopop singers]]\n[[Category:People from Pingtung County]]\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese composers]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Mandopop singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Gay musicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Taiwanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{infobox person\n| name = HUSH\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = Chen Jia-wei\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1985|1|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Pingtung City]], Taiwan\n| occupation = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter|lyricist}}\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present\n| module = {{Infobox Chinese|child=yes\n| t = \u9673\u5bb6\u5049\n}}\n| module2 = {{infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n | background = solo_singer\n| genre = {{hlist|[[Mandopop]]|rock}}\n| instrument = Voice, guitar, and piano\n| label = re:public records\n| associated_acts = {{hlist|[[A-Lin]]|[[Ding Dang (singer)|Ding Dang]]|[[Lala Hsu]]|[[Stephanie Sun]]}}\n}}\n}}\n'''Chen Jia-wei '''({{zh|c=\u9673\u5bb6\u5049}}; born 15 January 1985), better known by his stage name '''HUSH''', is a Taiwanese singer-songwriter and lyricist.\n\nHe is formerly the vocalist of the Taiwanese band hush! He has worked with artists like [[A-Lin]], [[Ding Dang (singer)|Ding Dang]], [[Lala Hsu]], and [[Stephanie Sun]].\n\n== Career ==\n\nWhile at [[National Pingtung Senior High School]], he was the lead singer of the pop music club. His interactions with the guitar club, which included future members of the band Mary See The Future ([[:zh:\u5148\u77e5\u746a\u8389|\u5148\u77e5\u746a\u8389]]), influenced him to learn guitar.<ref name=interview>{{cite web|title=\u5929\u6587\u7cfb\u7684\u6182\u9b31\u5c11\u5e74\uff0dhush\uff01 \u2013 \u97f3\u6a02\u5927\u4eba\u7269 \u2013 KKBOX|url=https://www.kkbox.com/tw/tc/column/interviews-0-255-1.html|website=KKBOX|accessdate=December 4, 2017|language=zh-TW}}</ref>\n\nHUSH majored in philosophy at [[Fu Jen Catholic University]].\n\nIn 2009, he signed with [[HIM International Music]] as a singer-songwriter, but he wasn't able to sell any songs. He also competed in the 3rd season of [[One Million Star]], which was won by Lala Hsu, but he was eliminated before the top 100.<ref name=interview />\n\nIn 2010, while working part-time at the coffee shop Kafka by the Sea in [[Gongguan, Taipei|Gongguan]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=\u516c\u95dc\u9054\u4eba|first1=\u5496\u5561\u9928|title=\u6d77\u908a\u7684\u5361\u592b\u5361--\u97f3\u6a02\u85dd\u6587\u7a7a\u9593 @ JuliePR \u5206\u4eab\u5de5\u4f5c\u8207\u73a9\u6a02 :: \u75de\u5ba2\u90a6 PIXNET ::|url=http://juliepr.pixnet.net/blog/post/27620380-%E6%B5%B7%E9%82%8A%E7%9A%84%E5%8D%A1%E5%A4%AB%E5%8D%A1--%E9%9F%B3%E6%A8%82%E8%97%9D%E6%96%87%E7%A9%BA%E9%96%93|website=JuliePR \u5206\u4eab\u5de5\u4f5c\u8207\u73a9\u6a02|accessdate=December 4, 2017|language=zh-TW}}</ref> he met drummer Bearpa and bassist Kabei. Together, they formed the band hush!<ref>{{cite web|title=HUSH|url=https://thewall.tw/artists/34|website=THE WALL MUSIC|accessdate=December 4, 2017|language=zh-TW}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Henley|first1=Joe|title=Live Wire: We\u2019ve got issues|url=http://www.taipeitimes.com/News/feat/archives/2014/01/03/2003580388|accessdate=January 23, 2018|work=Taipei Times|date=January 3, 2014}}</ref> Starting out acoustic, they transitioned into electric after playing many live shows. Usually, Hush records the demo and uploads to StreetVoice, a music-publishing platform for independent songwriters. His songs are inspired by his interests in astronomy, psychology, and tarot.<ref name=interview />\n\nWithin a year, they released an EP, ''Astronomical Cachet'' \u300e\u5929\u6587\u7279\u5fb5\u300f, and an album, ''X''. Popular in the indie scene, the band performed at various events and venues in [[Xian|Xi'an]], [[Shenzhen]], [[Taipei]], Hong Kong, and [[Kaohsiung]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ntdtv.com/xtr/b5/2015/04/05/a1189007.html|title=\u300c\u5929\u6587\u7cfb\u5275\u4f5c\u8a69\u4eba\u300d\u300c\u7b2c\u4e00\u4eba\u7a31\u300d\u9996\u5834\u5927\u578b\u500b\u5531 33\u9996HUSH\u8a69\u7bc7\u5f15\u7206\u5b64\u7368\u5b87\u5b99\uff01|date=April 4, 2015|publisher=\u65b0\u5510\u4eba|language=zh-hant|access-date=7 April 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414002145/http://www.ntdtv.com/xtr/b5/2015/04/05/a1189007.html|archive-date=April 14, 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter the band disbanded in 2014,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://playmusic.tw/column_info.php?id=2939&type=news|title=\u9f13\u624b\u718a\u7238\u9583\u96e2 Hush\uff01\u6a02\u5718\u3000\u6a02\u8ff7\u9707\u9a5a|date=November 16, 2014|publisher=PlayMusic|language=zh-hant|access-date=7 April 2015}}</ref> HUSH started his solo career. His first single was produced by [[Mayday (Taiwanese band)|Mayday]] bassist Masa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ettoday.net/news/20150317/479934.htm|title=HUSH\u56de\u6536\u300a\u514b\u535c\u52d2\u300b\u81ea\u5df1\u5531\u3000EP\u6f14\u5531\u6703\u6191\u9580\u7968\u514d\u8cbb\u9001|last=\u856d\u91c7\u8587|date=March 17, 2015|publisher=\u6771\u68ee\u65b0\u805e|language=zh-hant|access-date=7 April 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nHe has interests in [[astronomy]] and [[tarot]]. He is a supporter of [[same-sex marriage in Taiwan]],<ref>{{cite news|title=\u6f14\u5531\u51fa\u6ac3\u6b4c\u66f2 HUSH\uff1a\u6c92\u6709\u4eba\u7684\u611b\u662f\u9ad8\u5c1a\u6216\u5351\u5fae\u7684 {{!}} \u97f3\u6a02 {{!}} \u4e09\u7acb\u65b0\u805e\u7db2 SETN.COM|url=http://www.setn.com/News.aspx?NewsID=212230|accessdate=December 4, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u611b\u662f\u540c\u4e00\u500b\u7b54\u6848\uff01\u5c08\u8a2a HUSH\uff1a\u73fe\u5728\u662f 2015\uff0c\u6211\u662f GAY \u6709\u4ec0\u9ebc\u554f\u984c\u55ce\uff1f\uff5c\u5973\u4eba\u8ff7 Womany|url=http://womany.net/read/article/9415|website=\u5973\u4eba\u8ff7 womany.net|accessdate=December 4, 2017|language=zh-tw|date=December 17, 2015}}</ref> expressing his views in his song ''Same'' (\u540c\u4e00\u500b\u7b54\u6848).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.sina.com.tw/article/20150404/14122078.html|title=\u53f0\u7063\u6b4c\u624b\u88ab\u66dd\u540c\u6027\u6200 \u624b\u6a5f\u8edf\u9ad4\u4e0a\u627e\u7537\u4f34|date=April 4, 2015|publisher=\u5317\u4eac\u65b0\u6d6a\u7db2|language=zh-hant|access-date=5 April 2015}}</ref>\nHe came out during his concert on April 4, 2015.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u3010\u6211\u662f\u540c\u6027\u6200\u3011HUSH\uff1a\u5728\u6f14\u5531\u6703\u51fa\u6ac3\u662f\u6211\u5bb6\u7684\u4e8b {{!}} \u860b\u679c\u65e5\u5831|url=https://tw.appledaily.com/new/realtime/20161210/1008929/|accessdate=December 4, 2017|work=Apple Daily |language=zh-TW}}</ref> He's an avid participant of [[Taiwan Pride]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5716\uff0f\u6587\u9752\u7537\u795eHush\u73fe\u8eab\u5f69\u8679\u904a\u884c\u3000\u633a\u540c\u5fd7\u722d\u5a5a\u59fb\u5e73\u6b0a {{!}} ETtoday\u65b0\u805e\u96f2|url=https://www.ettoday.net/news/20161029/801815.htm|accessdate=December 4, 2017|work=ETtoday\u65b0\u805e\u96f2|language=zh-TW}}</ref>\n\n== Controversy ==\nIn 2015, the music video for his song ''King of Doubt (''\u6211\u60f3\u77e5\u9053\u4f60\u7684\u4e00\u5207) was banned from television broadcast for nudity.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://womany.net/read/article/9308|title=\u5beb\u5728 HUSH MV \u7981\u64ad\u5f8c\uff1a\u300c\u96e3\u9053\u4e0d\u70ba\u85dd\u8853\u812b\u8863\u670d\uff0c\u6211\u5c31\u9ad2\u6389\u4e86\u55ce\uff1f\u300d|work=\u5973\u4eba\u8ff7 womany.net|access-date=5 March 2017|language=zh-tw}}</ref> Regarding the ban, HUSH felt that \"it's good to open up a discussion about censorship and nudity,\" adding that \"people can find it on the internet anyway.\" A [[Virtual Reality|VR]] version of the music video was also made.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u5f71\uff0f\u4e0d\u754f\u7981\u64ad\u58d3\u529b HUSH\u9738\u6c23\u300c\u7981\u4e00\u652f\u62cd\u4e00\u652f\uff01\u300d\u2502\u5a1b\u6a02\u661f\u805e\u2502\u4e09\u7acb\u65b0\u805e\u7db2 SETN.COM|url=http://www.setn.com/E/News.aspx?NewsID=115463&From=Search&Key=hush}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n\n=== Releases ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"margin-bottom: 10px;\"\n! align=\"left\" width=\"60px\" | Type\n! align=\"left\" width=\"350px\" | Details\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | EP\n| align=\"left\" |''First Person Trilogy''  <br>'''\n\u7b2c\u4e00\u4eba\u7a31\u4e09\u90e8\u66f2\n* Released: March 20, 2015\n* Label: re: public records\n\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | Album\n| align=\"left\" |''Monopoly''<br>'''\n\u6a5f\u6703\u8207\u